channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Wall Street titan warns that job titles come and go but the only thing that matters is character
item.description: TIAA CEO Thasunda Brown Duckett insists she is not her title. ‘I earned it, but I don’t own it.’

item.title: It suddenly looks like there are too many homes for sale. Here's why that's not quite right
item.description: Inventory of both new and existing homes is finally rising, but the supply of newly built homes appears to be way too high.

item.title: Hopes for lower inflation are stifled by Wall Street’s expectations of Trump 2.0
VanEck and 21Shares file for Solana ETFs—a ‘bet’ on a Trump victory
item.description: The SEC has until March to decide on Solana ETFs. The real deadline, however, will be November's election.

item.title: First Ariane 6 rocket launches, as Europe rejoins a market dominated by Musk's SpaceX
item.description: The European Space Agency has prepared its newest heavy-lift Ariane 6 rocket to launch from Europe's Spaceport in Kourou, French Guiana on Tuesday.

item.title: Fast-food chains are now offering items for as low as $1.99
Barcelona residents are so fed up with tourism they’re squirting visitors with water guns as they try to enjoy their meals
item.description: Locals argue that tourism isn't helping with soaring housing costs, precarious employment, and a lower quality of life.

item.title: These software stocks have 'best of both worlds,' offering strong growth and solid balance sheets
item.description: As the artificial intelligence craze evolves, Canaccord Genuity thinks these software companies have strong fundamentals despite high interest rates.

item.title: The monthly jobs report keeps exaggerating U.S. employment gains
Retailer bans personal checks after rise in fraud
item.description: Walmart, Macy’s and Kohl’s are among the retailers that still accept personal checks at their stores.

item.title: UiPath to lay off 10% of workforce in companywide restructuring
item.description: Software developer UiPath will cut 10% of its workforce, or about 420 jobs, as part of a broader company restructuring.

item.title: Debt is fueling Americans’ summer fun. Many will be paying it off for years.
Microsoft ordered employees in China to only use iPhones due to security threats
item.description: The move is the latest example of the U.S. and China banning each other's tech products as the two superpowers build diverging digital ecosystems.

item.title: Senators seek special counsel probe of Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas
item.description: Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas "secretly accepted gifts and income potentially worth millions of dollars," the Democratic senators said evidence showed.

item.title: Amazon Prime Day has more travel deals this year. But here's what to avoid.
